reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Worked as Described
reviews.reviewText: I tried several wifi extenders to reach an area of my building under a concrete floor. None of them consistently kept an internet connection. This device worked like a charm and was up and running in 10 minutes. Plug the transmit end into a router port, take the recieve end near where you need internet, allow the two devices to sync, use the provided wifi SSID to connect to the reciever device. I'm not sure about the speed of the connection as I'm only using this to connect to a wifi connected sump pump for status updates but it works as described where others did not. Great product in my opinion.
